Police and bomb disposal officers have cordoned off a road in Dunoon in Argyll and Bute.
Restrictions have been put in place around the scene in the Castle Street area, close to the ferry terminal. 
A Police Scotland spokesman said: &quot;Police officers in Dunoon are dealing with an ongoing incident in the Castle Street area.
&quot;Cordons have been put in place to allow the incident to be managed.&quot;
